COVID-19 Status

As of 1:21AM PT jan-31, over 1.5 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 19.6 thousand have died.

In the last day, 1.7 thousand new infections were reported and 6 deaths. Currently 1,534 are in the hospital and 40 are in the ICU. This is trending upwards.

Fortunately, 25.1 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. For those 5 years and older, 35.8% have their 1st shot and 19.8% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is slowing down, but there are -2 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~-995 days for new deliveries to get into arms.

At the current rate, Canadians should achieve herd immunity around when 80% of the entire population is fully vaccinated. There is no approved vaccine for children under 5.

  • 107 in 100 have at least one vaccine dose,
    77 in 100 are fully vaccinated.
    41 in 100 have been boosted.
    Herd immunity is estimated at ~85%
